    <thetext>The wording &quot;It may have an exponent of ten&quot; in Section 8 is highly misleading. I interpreted this as e.g. something like the number 1.1 (mantissa in technical terms) having an exponent of 10, and thus a value of 1.1 to the power of 10, i.e. 2.5937424601. But this is surely not what&apos;s meant, and I&apos;m sure the language can be improved to avoid misunderstandings such as the above.</thetext>
